1
00:00:01,869 --> 00:00:03,904
- Polnareff: What is that?
- ( Iggy growls )

2
00:00:03,937 --> 00:00:05,372
polnareff:
Weren’t avdol’s flames

3
00:00:05,405 --> 00:00:07,374
supposed to be
able to sense anything?

4
00:00:07,407 --> 00:00:09,442
Avdol, where are you?!

5
00:00:09,476 --> 00:00:12,012
( Stand growls ) Avdol...

6
00:00:12,045 --> 00:00:15,248
Has been reduced
to nothingness.

7
00:00:15,282 --> 00:00:16,550
You were arrogant enough

8
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:18,985
to believe
you could defeat lord dio.

9
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:22,990
Allow me to demonstrate
just how wrong you were.

10
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:27,060
( Polnareff gasps )

11
00:00:27,094 --> 00:00:29,997
Cool ice: You’ll fall
in line one by one

12
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:32,466
as I scatter
your atomic fragments

13
00:00:32,499 --> 00:00:34,468
across the recesses of the void.

14
00:00:34,501 --> 00:00:35,569
( Both gasp )

15
00:00:35,602 --> 00:00:38,171
( Stand growls )

16
00:00:40,607 --> 00:00:42,275
( Polnareff gasps )
It can’t be.

17
00:00:44,011 --> 00:00:45,479
I don’t believe you.

18
00:00:45,512 --> 00:00:47,481
Avdol’s not dead.

19
00:00:48,515 --> 00:00:51,618
Don’t you lie to me!

20
00:00:52,853 --> 00:00:54,421
Stand: W-what?!

21
00:00:54,454 --> 00:00:57,190
I never would have imagined
polnareff’s stand

22
00:00:57,224 --> 00:00:59,960
could attack this swiftly
from so far away.

23
00:00:59,993 --> 00:01:02,028
An amazing feat, to be sure.

24
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:03,363
Silver chariot: Over here.

25
00:01:03,397 --> 00:01:06,000
I want you to look at me
when I kill you.

26
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:08,368
( Polnareff yells )

27
00:01:08,402 --> 00:01:10,170
♪

28
00:01:11,972 --> 00:01:13,140
( Iggy yelps )

29
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:15,575
( Polnareff screams )

30
00:01:15,609 --> 00:01:17,611
♪

31
00:01:19,646 --> 00:01:21,648
( Singing in Japanese )

32
00:01:40,634 --> 00:01:42,536
( Rubble falling )

33
00:01:42,569 --> 00:01:44,371
- men: Hmm?
- Joseph: All right,

34
00:01:44,404 --> 00:01:46,640
now i’m sure
something fishy’s going on.

35
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:48,375
ever since
we escaped the mirage,

36
00:01:48,408 --> 00:01:50,377
i’ve heard
the sounds of a battle.

37
00:01:50,410 --> 00:01:53,046
Kakyoin: Blast it. Avdol
and polnareff are out there.

38
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:55,316
- Joseph: Hmm?
- Jotaro: Mm.

39
00:01:55,349 --> 00:01:57,384
( Polnareff panting )

40
00:01:57,417 --> 00:01:59,920
damn that guy.
I know I hit the bastard,

41
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:01,621
but it wasn’t
enough to kill him.

42
00:02:01,655 --> 00:02:05,159
He just swallowed himself again
so he could hide in that abyss.

43
00:02:05,192 --> 00:02:06,894
Damn that guy and his stand.

44
00:02:06,927 --> 00:02:08,929
( Iggy whimpering )

45
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:13,066
( Polnareff gasps )

46
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:15,402
( Woman vocalizing )

47
00:02:15,435 --> 00:02:18,238
Polnareff: Avdol,
how could you do that?

48
00:02:18,272 --> 00:02:21,208
How could you break
the one rule you gave us?

49
00:02:21,241 --> 00:02:24,544
avdol: Polnareff, iggy,
you have to get out of here now!

50
00:02:24,578 --> 00:02:27,514
polnareff: You told us
we had to watch our own backs,

51
00:02:27,548 --> 00:02:31,052
that you wouldn’t save us,
even if we were in danger.

52
00:02:31,084 --> 00:02:32,652
You liar.

53
00:02:34,288 --> 00:02:36,657
You’ve been meddling
in other people’s business

54
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:39,960
ever since the moment
we set foot in India.

55
00:02:39,993 --> 00:02:41,361
Damn it, avdol!

56
00:02:41,395 --> 00:02:43,097
Why couldn’t you
just leave me alone

57
00:02:43,130 --> 00:02:45,132
and mind your own
freaking business?!

58
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:47,000
( Both gasp )

59
00:02:48,068 --> 00:02:49,436
Polnareff: If I hadn’t ducked,

60
00:02:49,469 --> 00:02:51,538
i’d be a dead man right now.

61
00:02:51,572 --> 00:02:55,109
it’s like fate
is telling me to carry on.

62
00:02:55,142 --> 00:02:58,479
This must be avdol’s way
of knocking some sense into me.

63
00:03:03,417 --> 00:03:05,185
( Iggy growls )

64
00:03:05,219 --> 00:03:06,654
♪

65
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:08,989
( The fool growls )

66
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:14,628
Polnareff: It’s way
too dangerous in here.

67
00:03:14,661 --> 00:03:17,230
Let’s get moving!

68
00:03:17,264 --> 00:03:18,632
( Iggy barks )

69
00:03:18,665 --> 00:03:20,734
♪

70
00:03:25,606 --> 00:03:28,409
Polnareff: Come on, iggy.
We have to make it upstairs!

71
00:03:28,442 --> 00:03:30,210
Don’t fall behind!

72
00:03:38,118 --> 00:03:40,153
( Gasps ) Look up ahead!

73
00:03:40,187 --> 00:03:42,322
It’s the exit!
We’re almost there!

74
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:46,359
But I won’t just turn tail
and run away.

75
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:47,628
( Iggy gasps )

76
00:03:47,661 --> 00:03:50,164
polnareff:
Avdol sacrificed himself for us,

77
00:03:50,197 --> 00:03:52,399
and i’ll repay that debt,
no matter what!

78
00:03:52,432 --> 00:03:53,566
He believed we had the power

79
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,769
to put an end to dio
once and for all.

80
00:03:55,802 --> 00:03:58,738
I can’t betray his faith in us
by letting him down.

81
00:03:58,772 --> 00:04:00,173
That is not an option.

82
00:04:02,209 --> 00:04:06,380
I refuse to take the easy way
out like some common coward.

83
00:04:06,413 --> 00:04:09,116
I’m gonna see this fight through
to the bitter end!

84
00:04:09,149 --> 00:04:13,220
The only place i’m running to
is dio’s shadow den!

85
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:15,655
♪

86
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,326
( Iggy growls )

87
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:20,427
( Barks )

88
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:23,296
polnareff:
So up the stairs we go!

89
00:04:27,067 --> 00:04:29,069
♪

90
00:04:31,238 --> 00:04:33,707
Stand: I expected him
to dash out the door.

91
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:35,842
( Chuckles )
Pity.

92
00:04:37,744 --> 00:04:40,714
Cool ice: Impressive.
He managed a hit.

93
00:04:40,747 --> 00:04:43,450
it seems
polnareff’s mental fortitude

94
00:04:43,483 --> 00:04:45,618
gives him the ability
to conquer his fears

95
00:04:45,652 --> 00:04:47,454
in the face of imminent death.

96
00:04:47,487 --> 00:04:51,458
You will soon be joining avdol.
Rest assured.

97
00:04:51,491 --> 00:04:53,393
Your strength
pales in comparison

98
00:04:53,427 --> 00:04:56,363
to the harbinger of death
that is my stand.

99
00:04:57,598 --> 00:04:59,467
polnareff:
If what he says is true,

100
00:04:59,500 --> 00:05:02,203
his stand’s jaws are the gateway
to an alternate dimension,

101
00:05:02,236 --> 00:05:04,672
a dark, unimaginable abyss,

102
00:05:04,705 --> 00:05:07,174
one that allows him
to move through our realm

103
00:05:07,207 --> 00:05:08,709
without leaving
any trace of himself.

104
00:05:10,644 --> 00:05:13,280
But how does he do it?

105
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:16,550
and how the heck
am I supposed to beat him?

106
00:05:17,718 --> 00:05:19,720
- ( Iggy yelps )
- ( Polnareff gasps )

107
00:05:21,555 --> 00:05:23,724
♪

108
00:05:23,757 --> 00:05:25,792
No, no, no! He’s cut us off!

109
00:05:27,294 --> 00:05:28,762
He’s nearby.

110
00:05:28,795 --> 00:05:30,363
But where exactly?

111
00:05:30,397 --> 00:05:32,599
Iggy, I need you
to watch my back,

112
00:05:33,634 --> 00:05:34,735
and don’t worry.

113
00:05:34,768 --> 00:05:36,770
I’ll do the same for you.

114
00:05:52,619 --> 00:05:55,322
Okay, if he wants to reach us,

115
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:58,191
then he’s gonna have
to come out of that other realm.

116
00:05:58,225 --> 00:05:59,893
This is good.
He has to come out

117
00:05:59,927 --> 00:06:01,562
from the dark beyond
at some point.

118
00:06:01,595 --> 00:06:03,831
When he does,
i’ll take my chance

119
00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:06,200
and attack him
with everything i’ve got.

120
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:08,769
All right, come at me,
you demented pinball!

121
00:06:08,802 --> 00:06:10,504
I’ll slice you in two!

122
00:06:10,537 --> 00:06:12,305
Now i’m pissed off,

123
00:06:12,339 --> 00:06:13,874
so my chariot’s even faster!

124
00:06:13,907 --> 00:06:15,642
I may have lost avdol,

125
00:06:15,676 --> 00:06:18,612
but it’ll be a cold day in hell
before I let you get away.

126
00:06:20,547 --> 00:06:22,849
( Gasps ) Huh?

127
00:06:34,695 --> 00:06:36,597
Eh?

128
00:06:37,631 --> 00:06:38,665
What the hell?!

129
00:06:38,699 --> 00:06:41,202
He--he was hiding under my foot?

130
00:06:41,235 --> 00:06:42,403
Chario--

131
00:06:47,274 --> 00:06:48,242
( groans )

132
00:06:48,275 --> 00:06:50,277
( Wailing )

133
00:06:51,745 --> 00:06:53,447
Aah! My foot!

134
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,749
Stand: Now you can’t run away.

135
00:06:55,782 --> 00:06:57,684
- ( Polnareff groaning )
- Stand: I got your foot

136
00:06:57,718 --> 00:07:00,221
so that you can’t hide anymore.

137
00:07:00,254 --> 00:07:01,322
( The fool growls )

138
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:05,759
Polnareff: Eat silver.

139
00:07:05,792 --> 00:07:07,260
Stand: I’ll pass.

140
00:07:07,294 --> 00:07:09,563
( Silver chariot yelling )

141
00:07:19,907 --> 00:07:22,743
Kakyoin: Mr. Joestar,
a brawl’s under way.

142
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:24,211
Joseph: Avdol and polnareff.

143
00:07:24,244 --> 00:07:25,979
sounds like
they came in after us

144
00:07:26,013 --> 00:07:27,748
and wound up getting themselves
into a fight.

145
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:31,718
come on, you two!
We have to find them asap!

146
00:07:33,687 --> 00:07:36,323
♪

147
00:07:36,356 --> 00:07:40,927
Cool ice: You’ve managed to hide
amid the chaos, polnareff.

148
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:45,399
How futile. You couldn’t have
gone far with that injury,

149
00:07:45,432 --> 00:07:48,402
which means you’re hiding
beneath the rubble.

150
00:07:51,371 --> 00:07:53,573
- ( Stand growls )
- Cool ice: By now,

151
00:07:53,607 --> 00:07:56,009
you must have realized
you’re helpless against me.

152
00:07:56,043 --> 00:07:58,779
You shall meet your end
by my hand.

153
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:02,649
now then,
where could you be, polnareff?

154
00:08:02,683 --> 00:08:04,952
Dio: That’s quite the ruckus,
cool ice.

155
00:08:04,985 --> 00:08:05,986
( Cool ice gasps )

156
00:08:08,922 --> 00:08:12,492
( Gasps ) L-lord dio.

157
00:08:12,526 --> 00:08:14,028
♪

158
00:08:14,061 --> 00:08:16,497
Please be careful, my lord.

159
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:18,665
i believe polnareff
and that four-legged rodent

160
00:08:18,699 --> 00:08:20,301
are still hiding nearby.

161
00:08:20,334 --> 00:08:22,670
Allow me to handle
the situation.

162
00:08:22,703 --> 00:08:25,573
You mustn’t trouble yourself
with such nonsense, master.

163
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:38,051
( Iggy whines )

164
00:08:38,085 --> 00:08:42,489
polnareff: A fake dio
made from the fool. We got him.

165
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:44,625
You’d think i’d feel guilty

166
00:08:44,658 --> 00:08:47,327
about attacking from behind
like a coward,

167
00:08:47,361 --> 00:08:48,963
and you’d be wrong,

168
00:08:48,996 --> 00:08:51,699
because you pulled
the same shit on avdol.

169
00:08:51,732 --> 00:08:53,867
This is the death you deserve.

170
00:08:53,901 --> 00:08:55,970
Now, iggy! Crucify him.

171
00:08:56,003 --> 00:08:58,005
♪

172
00:09:00,674 --> 00:09:02,176
Crucify him!

173
00:09:02,209 --> 00:09:04,044
Make him pay for what he did.

174
00:09:04,077 --> 00:09:07,247
End his life in the same
merciless way he did avdol’s.

175
00:09:07,281 --> 00:09:08,849
Send him straight to hell!

176
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:13,153
( Both gasp )

177
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:16,056
Polnareff: You’re kidding?!

178
00:09:16,089 --> 00:09:18,725
He knows. But how?!

179
00:09:18,759 --> 00:09:20,394
Cool ice: Because
the windows to my left

180
00:09:20,427 --> 00:09:22,796
are letting in
the light from the sun.

181
00:09:22,830 --> 00:09:27,335
Lord dio would never enter
this room during the day.

182
00:09:27,367 --> 00:09:30,203
You’ll suffer a thousand deaths
for your deception.

183
00:09:30,237 --> 00:09:32,206
Polnareff: Iggy.

184
00:09:38,378 --> 00:09:39,412
( Iggy whimpers )

185
00:09:39,446 --> 00:09:41,448
( Yelps )

186
00:09:41,481 --> 00:09:43,483
cool ice:
I made a vow to lord dio

187
00:09:43,517 --> 00:09:45,119
that I would kill
you interlopers.

188
00:09:45,152 --> 00:09:47,054
He entrusted me
with that honor.

189
00:09:47,087 --> 00:09:48,989
Lord dio’s a man of his word.

190
00:09:49,022 --> 00:09:51,791
He would never descend to
the second floor for any reason.

191
00:09:51,825 --> 00:09:54,394
Polnareff: No.
He’s gonna kill iggy.

192
00:09:54,428 --> 00:09:57,164
He’s about to be
swallowed by the abyss!

193
00:09:57,197 --> 00:09:59,966
Cool ice: Now die,
you filthy, pathetic dog.

194
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,171
Your incorrigible ruse forced me
to destroy lord dio’s likeness!

195
00:10:04,204 --> 00:10:06,506
( Iggy yelps )

196
00:10:06,540 --> 00:10:09,143
♪

197
00:10:11,144 --> 00:10:12,312
( Polnareff gasps )

198
00:10:12,346 --> 00:10:15,082
D-did he really just hit him?

199
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:16,917
He didn’t use the void.

200
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:20,086
Instead of killing iggy,
he went in for a punch!

201
00:10:21,488 --> 00:10:24,291
cool ice:
Do you know what you’ve done?

202
00:10:24,324 --> 00:10:26,259
I don’t care if it was a fake.

203
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:27,461
You forced me to destroy

204
00:10:27,494 --> 00:10:29,396
a figure
in the form of lord dio,

205
00:10:29,429 --> 00:10:32,032
and you must answer
for that crime.

206
00:10:33,233 --> 00:10:35,001
Your life is mine now!

207
00:10:35,035 --> 00:10:38,338
I will kick you to death!
( Growls )

208
00:10:38,372 --> 00:10:40,307
( Iggy gags )

209
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:43,877
Cool ice: My dark abyss could
swallow you whole in an instant,

210
00:10:43,911 --> 00:10:46,113
but a quick death
wouldn’t satiate my fury.

211
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:48,448
- ( Iggy gags )
- Cool ice: This whole mess,

212
00:10:48,482 --> 00:10:50,117
it’s all your fault!

213
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:52,853
This is what happens
to those who anger me.

214
00:10:52,886 --> 00:10:54,488
Have you learned
your lesson yet?!

215
00:10:54,521 --> 00:10:57,057
How ’bout it? Is this better?

216
00:10:57,090 --> 00:11:00,493
Tell me! Is it? Is it?! Is it?!

217
00:11:00,527 --> 00:11:01,495
( Polnareff gasps )

218
00:11:01,528 --> 00:11:04,131
Stop it! Leave him alone!

219
00:11:04,164 --> 00:11:06,800
It’s like cool ice’s brain
has melted.

220
00:11:06,834 --> 00:11:09,036
Is he really going bat-shit
because he destroyed

221
00:11:09,069 --> 00:11:12,139
some pile of sand
that looked like dio?

222
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:14,841
from over here,
his soul is the murky abyss.

223
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:16,543
It’s a bottomless black hole

224
00:11:16,577 --> 00:11:20,214
that obliterates any and every
thing that gets in its way.

225
00:11:22,082 --> 00:11:24,151
Cool ice: I was warned
about the humans.

226
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:26,186
lord dio said
the resolve in their hearts

227
00:11:26,220 --> 00:11:27,922
must never be underestimated.

228
00:11:27,955 --> 00:11:31,826
But you, you’re just
a flea-bitten stray.

229
00:11:31,859 --> 00:11:33,194
You’ve never known resolve,

230
00:11:33,227 --> 00:11:36,530
and you certainly
know nothing of pride.

231
00:11:36,563 --> 00:11:37,831
( Iggy chuckles )

232
00:11:37,865 --> 00:11:39,900
( Cool ice gasps )

233
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:41,268
Yeah? Grin at this!

234
00:11:41,301 --> 00:11:43,136
Polnareff: Leave him alone.

235
00:11:43,170 --> 00:11:44,571
cool ice:
You like that? Do you?!

236
00:11:44,605 --> 00:11:46,574
Polnareff: What did I say?

237
00:11:46,607 --> 00:11:48,976
cool ice: Come on!
Your suffering’s just begun.

238
00:11:49,009 --> 00:11:52,846
Polnareff: Cool ice!
You’re dealing with me now!

239
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,215
( Squelch )

240
00:11:54,248 --> 00:11:56,217
( Cool ice sighs )

241
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:58,552
I’m ending this, polnareff.

242
00:11:58,585 --> 00:12:00,153
( Silver chariot yelling )

243
00:12:05,325 --> 00:12:06,993
Polnareff: Damn it.

244
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:09,596
He’s gone!

245
00:12:09,630 --> 00:12:12,199
But more importantly, iggy,

246
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,901
our plan to trick cool ice
may have fallen through,

247
00:12:14,935 --> 00:12:17,171
but your sand
might have just saved us.

248
00:12:17,204 --> 00:12:20,274
Thanks to you, I think I found
a way to find the bastard.

249
00:12:20,307 --> 00:12:22,976
♪

250
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:32,018
Yeah, that’s him, all right.

251
00:12:32,052 --> 00:12:33,620
I can see him moving around.

252
00:12:33,654 --> 00:12:37,391
Guess your stand power
is a double-edged sword.

253
00:12:37,424 --> 00:12:39,993
when you move,
your stand has no choice

254
00:12:40,027 --> 00:12:42,296
but to absorb
everything in your path.

255
00:12:42,329 --> 00:12:44,331
So choke on a mouthful of this,

256
00:12:44,364 --> 00:12:46,900
and get over here,
you piece of shit.

257
00:12:46,934 --> 00:12:48,402
As soon as you come out

258
00:12:48,435 --> 00:12:51,605
from behind your stand’s
putrid teeth to attack me,

259
00:12:51,638 --> 00:12:54,207
i’ll turn the tables
and finish you off.

260
00:12:54,241 --> 00:12:55,209
( Cool ice gags )

261
00:12:55,242 --> 00:12:56,443
Polnareff: Bull’s-eye!

262
00:12:56,476 --> 00:12:58,979
Yeah, eat that.

263
00:12:59,012 --> 00:13:00,313
Well, would you look at that?

264
00:13:00,347 --> 00:13:02,349
I found your weakness,
cool ice.

265
00:13:02,382 --> 00:13:05,619
Any attempt to pinpoint my
location leaves you vulnerable,

266
00:13:05,652 --> 00:13:07,654
which is probably
a tad inconvenient,

267
00:13:07,688 --> 00:13:09,290
since you can’t see me

268
00:13:09,323 --> 00:13:11,158
without emerging
from your dark dimension.

269
00:13:11,191 --> 00:13:12,426
( Cool ice gagging )

270
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:13,560
Polnareff: It’s over.

271
00:13:13,594 --> 00:13:15,129
Now suck on my sword

272
00:13:15,162 --> 00:13:16,563
and burn in hell, fils de pute!

273
00:13:16,597 --> 00:13:19,233
Hurry up, and die.

274
00:13:19,266 --> 00:13:20,267
( Cool ice growls )

275
00:13:23,337 --> 00:13:25,606
( Polnareff gagging )

276
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:27,941
( Cool ice growling )

277
00:13:27,975 --> 00:13:30,444
Polnareff: W-what?
How are you still alive?

278
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:33,113
I skewered your throat
and brainstem.

279
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:34,948
Would you die, already?!

280
00:13:34,982 --> 00:13:36,717
No way you’re getting out of it.

281
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:39,052
Hurry up, and die!

282
00:13:39,086 --> 00:13:41,121
( Cool ice gasping )

283
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:45,625
Polnareff: Stop making me
repeat myself. Die!

284
00:13:45,659 --> 00:13:48,428
( Gagging )

285
00:13:48,462 --> 00:13:50,230
Cool ice: I cannot die.

286
00:13:50,264 --> 00:13:53,033
My mission is far too important
to feel any pain.

287
00:13:53,066 --> 00:13:55,569
I will not rest
until I kill you.

288
00:13:55,602 --> 00:13:57,170
I’ll swallow iggy, the joestars,

289
00:13:57,204 --> 00:13:59,406
and anyone else
who gets in my way.

290
00:13:59,439 --> 00:14:02,142
Only after your deaths
will I allow myself to die.

291
00:14:02,176 --> 00:14:04,445
( Polnareff shrieking )

292
00:14:07,648 --> 00:14:09,250
( Screams )

293
00:14:09,283 --> 00:14:10,751
Silver chariot: Bastard!

294
00:14:10,784 --> 00:14:12,152
Cool ice: There’s a good boy.

295
00:14:12,186 --> 00:14:13,721
You knew to withdraw your sword.

296
00:14:13,754 --> 00:14:16,423
Silver chariot: I also know
that you’re about to die.

297
00:14:18,192 --> 00:14:19,760
( Polnareff gasps )

298
00:14:19,793 --> 00:14:21,561
Cool ice: This is the one,

299
00:14:21,595 --> 00:14:23,530
the vile arm
you used to stab me.

300
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:25,532
( Polnareff screams )

301
00:14:27,534 --> 00:14:29,669
( Grunting )

302
00:14:29,703 --> 00:14:31,338
Knock it off!

303
00:14:32,339 --> 00:14:33,507
Silver chariot: Damn it!

304
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:35,709
I had no choice
but to shove him away.

305
00:14:35,742 --> 00:14:37,711
- no!
- ( Cream laughing )

306
00:14:37,744 --> 00:14:39,713
silver chariot:
Y-you’re not going anywhere!

307
00:14:42,216 --> 00:14:44,785
did I get him?
Ah, where’d he go now?

308
00:14:44,818 --> 00:14:47,421
- ( Groans )
- ( Polnareff groans )

309
00:14:47,454 --> 00:14:51,191
Shit. He got my leg.
I can’t move.

310
00:14:51,225 --> 00:14:53,761
but I can’t think
about the pain right now.

311
00:14:53,794 --> 00:14:55,396
I was so close.

312
00:14:55,429 --> 00:14:57,698
I almost managed
to land a killing blow,

313
00:14:57,731 --> 00:14:59,499
but he got away.

314
00:14:59,533 --> 00:15:03,370
This guy is different,
fueled by pure vengeance.

315
00:15:03,403 --> 00:15:04,738
And he’s not just nuts.

316
00:15:04,771 --> 00:15:07,507
His devotion to dio
is all-consuming.

317
00:15:07,541 --> 00:15:10,210
But I won’t let him
get the upper hand.

318
00:15:10,244 --> 00:15:12,113
You said you couldn’t die yet?

319
00:15:12,145 --> 00:15:15,115
Well, I can’t die
until I kill you!

320
00:15:16,316 --> 00:15:18,084
Okay, here he comes.

321
00:15:18,118 --> 00:15:19,186
Take this!

322
00:15:21,221 --> 00:15:22,556
Shit, it’s no use.

323
00:15:22,589 --> 00:15:25,292
His stand just obliterated
the tip of my sword,

324
00:15:25,325 --> 00:15:28,228
though it probably wouldn’t
matter, even if it were intact.

325
00:15:28,262 --> 00:15:31,098
It’s impossible to attack him
when he’s hidden in the abyss.

326
00:15:31,131 --> 00:15:32,566
if I so much
as touch that thing,

327
00:15:32,599 --> 00:15:34,434
it’ll swallow me whole.

328
00:15:34,468 --> 00:15:37,171
( Silver chariot gasps )

329
00:15:37,204 --> 00:15:40,741
Great, now he’s absorbing
the building at random. Merde!

330
00:15:43,577 --> 00:15:45,779
Polnareff: That’s clever.
He knows full well

331
00:15:45,812 --> 00:15:47,681
i’ll go after him
if he shows himself,

332
00:15:47,714 --> 00:15:50,283
so he’s blindly attacking to
prevent me from fighting back.

333
00:15:51,418 --> 00:15:52,719
He’s not messing around.

334
00:15:52,753 --> 00:15:55,422
at this rate,
he’s gonna hit me for sure.

335
00:15:55,455 --> 00:15:58,358
I should pull back chariot
and think of a plan.

336
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:06,500
Damn. This isn’t good.

337
00:16:06,533 --> 00:16:09,136
Iggy’s not gonna last long
if he keeps losing blood.

338
00:16:09,169 --> 00:16:10,637
From the state he’s in,

339
00:16:10,671 --> 00:16:13,274
i’d say his broken ribs
must have punctured his lungs.

340
00:16:13,307 --> 00:16:14,775
( Gasps )

341
00:16:21,348 --> 00:16:23,817
And just when I thought
this couldn’t get any worse.

342
00:16:23,851 --> 00:16:26,654
why the hell
is he devouring the walls?

343
00:16:29,323 --> 00:16:32,593
Wait a second. I’m starting
to think I was all wrong.

344
00:16:32,626 --> 00:16:34,161
This isn’t random.

345
00:16:34,194 --> 00:16:36,396
It was all part of his plan
from the beginning.

346
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:39,300
He’s been drawing circles
around me,

347
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:42,369
and with every lap,
he’s getting closer and closer.

348
00:16:43,470 --> 00:16:45,405
The odds are stacked against me,

349
00:16:45,439 --> 00:16:47,207
but I have to do something.

350
00:16:47,241 --> 00:16:49,176
He’s closing in.

351
00:16:49,209 --> 00:16:51,178
He still doesn’t know
our location,

352
00:16:51,211 --> 00:16:53,480
but with that rolling ball
of death hurtling toward us,

353
00:16:53,514 --> 00:16:54,682
it doesn’t matter.

354
00:16:54,715 --> 00:16:57,718
he’s got us
right where he wants us.

355
00:16:57,751 --> 00:17:00,887
There’s no way i’m gonna be able
to dodge an attack from him

356
00:17:00,921 --> 00:17:03,323
with this bum leg.

357
00:17:03,357 --> 00:17:06,627
i-i’ve got to try
to escape through the floor.

358
00:17:09,263 --> 00:17:11,732
I don’t have enough time
to tunnel through!

359
00:17:11,765 --> 00:17:13,934
He’s coming straight for us!

360
00:17:17,738 --> 00:17:19,773
Somehow, I dodged it.

361
00:17:19,806 --> 00:17:22,509
Not out of the woods.
He’s closing in on me

362
00:17:22,543 --> 00:17:24,712
like a needle
on an old record player.

363
00:17:24,745 --> 00:17:26,513
i only have
about five more rounds

364
00:17:26,547 --> 00:17:27,782
before he makes
his way back here

365
00:17:27,814 --> 00:17:29,749
and finishes me off for good.

366
00:17:29,783 --> 00:17:32,352
So, the million-dollar question

367
00:17:32,386 --> 00:17:35,389
is how do I dodge
with this injured leg?

368
00:17:35,422 --> 00:17:37,424
♪

369
00:17:47,434 --> 00:17:50,704
If I had it my way,
i’d just pick option two,

370
00:17:50,737 --> 00:17:52,339
but I can’t count on that.

371
00:17:52,372 --> 00:17:54,741
They only entered the mansion
10 minutes before us.

372
00:17:54,775 --> 00:17:57,811
As much as i’d love for them
to swoop in out of thin air

373
00:17:57,845 --> 00:18:00,614
and save the day like
some American comic book hero,

374
00:18:00,647 --> 00:18:02,916
wishful thinking’s
not gonna save me now.

375
00:18:02,950 --> 00:18:05,853
There’s no point hoping
for an out-of-the-blue rescue.

376
00:18:05,886 --> 00:18:07,821
For all I know,
the others might be

377
00:18:07,855 --> 00:18:10,024
in the middle of a fight
themselves.

378
00:18:11,258 --> 00:18:12,392
All right then.

379
00:18:12,426 --> 00:18:14,428
Option one’s our only choice.

380
00:18:18,298 --> 00:18:20,400
Okay, chariot,
I need you to pull me

381
00:18:20,434 --> 00:18:23,270
out of the circle
as fast as you can.

382
00:18:23,303 --> 00:18:25,272
( Grunting )

383
00:18:27,708 --> 00:18:29,476
What are you doing?

384
00:18:29,510 --> 00:18:31,545
Pull me faster, chariot!

385
00:18:35,849 --> 00:18:38,418
I-it’s no use.

386
00:18:38,452 --> 00:18:40,287
♪

387
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:41,588
Narrator: What do you know?

388
00:18:41,622 --> 00:18:44,425
The answer ended up
being option three.

389
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:46,694
Life’s a bitch.

390
00:18:47,928 --> 00:18:49,563
Polnareff: Silver chariot

391
00:18:49,596 --> 00:18:51,932
is a finesse-oriented stand
that fights with a saber.

392
00:18:51,965 --> 00:18:55,302
It simply doesn’t have the power
to pull my body weight,

393
00:18:55,335 --> 00:18:56,937
especially when i’m injured.

394
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:59,406
I’m done for.

395
00:19:02,776 --> 00:19:04,778
♪

396
00:19:13,987 --> 00:19:15,789
You’re holding on by a thread.

397
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:17,557
Stay down, you stupid mutt.

398
00:19:17,591 --> 00:19:20,627
if you keep moving or
try using your stand’s power,

399
00:19:20,661 --> 00:19:23,030
your broken ribs will sink
deeper into your lungs

400
00:19:23,063 --> 00:19:24,965
and kill you.

401
00:19:30,003 --> 00:19:32,572
hey, you can drop
the tough guy act, you idiot.

402
00:19:32,606 --> 00:19:34,374
The only thing
this will accomplish

403
00:19:34,408 --> 00:19:35,976
is you dying
right along with me.

404
00:19:41,014 --> 00:19:44,084
Just you wait. I’m the one
who’s gonna save you.

405
00:19:44,117 --> 00:19:46,786
You have to live on
to tell Mr. Joestar

406
00:19:46,820 --> 00:19:48,488
and the others
about this bastard.

407
00:19:48,522 --> 00:19:50,858
You have to defeat him
in my stead.

408
00:19:50,891 --> 00:19:54,628
Avdol might have saved me,
but you sure as hell better not!

409
00:19:54,661 --> 00:19:57,731
if we all die here,
then what was the point of this?

410
00:19:57,764 --> 00:19:59,532
- ( Iggy gasps )
- ( Polnareff grunting )

411
00:19:59,566 --> 00:20:01,535
( Chorus vocalizing )

412
00:20:01,568 --> 00:20:04,004
One more loop,
and its lights out.

413
00:20:04,037 --> 00:20:05,939
So it’s number three.

414
00:20:05,973 --> 00:20:08,642
Life can be a bitch sometimes.

415
00:20:09,676 --> 00:20:11,745
We both wanted to win.

416
00:20:11,778 --> 00:20:13,546
Guess he wanted it more.

417
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:14,948
( Iggy gasps )

418
00:20:17,584 --> 00:20:20,554
Polnareff: Au revoir, iggy.

419
00:20:20,587 --> 00:20:22,756
( Iggy squeals )

420
00:20:25,592 --> 00:20:27,761
( Yelps )

421
00:20:38,605 --> 00:20:40,774
( Clang echoes )

422
00:20:44,011 --> 00:20:46,013
♪

